    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Right Switch Panel</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Removal</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Locate and remove the forward edge mounting bolts along the lower windshield seal.
                    Loosen and remove the mounting bolts.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Slide the driver side window forward section open to access the mounting screw at the
                    left hand corner of the dash panel assembly. Loosen and remove the mounting screw.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Locate the right wing switch panel, locate and remove any optional equipment mountings
                    that may be mounted to the right wing switch panel; e.g., communication radio microphone (
                    <hotlnk document="s47005_14.xml" xrefid="f4700553">Figure 53</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f47005144" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g47005144.webp" filename="../figg47/g47005144.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="248px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 144. Right Wing Switch Panel Removal</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">DRIVER RIGHT WING PANEL</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">RIGHT WING SWITCH PANEL</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">RIGHT WING SWITCH PANEL MOUNTING SCREWS</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">To remove right wing switch panel, locate the four mounting screws (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f47005144">Fig. 144, Item 3</hotlnk>) attaching the switch panel assembly. Loosen
                    and remove.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove the switch panel assembly and disconnect harness connections if necessary.</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcsubproc>
